we can use Atom editor to create a prototype of Comshell;

; sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xinit xf86-video-{intel,nouveau,amdgpu} i3-wm atom
; cp ./Atom/* ~/.atom/
; nano ~/.bash_profile
  startx
; nano ~/.xinitrc
  exec i3
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3
; nano ~/.config/i3/config
  # i3 config file (v4)
  default_border none
  exec atom

"https://discuss.atom.io/t/creating-a-better-kiosk-with-electron/19443"
when Ozone backend for Chromium is ready, and is available in Electron,
  we can use its DRM/GBM platform, and run Atom without the need for X11 or Wayland;
"https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/master/docs/ozone_overview.md"
